  "text": "Another consideration is that the participants of both the NHS and the HPFS are 90% white. Thus, our results may not be widely generalizable to populations with higher percentages of minorities, particularly those of African or Caribbean heritage who are at greater risk of POAG [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
